parameters:
\n<Lyric>"Sniff... Ugh... It's cold, water got in my nose and it
really hurts, this is the worst..."
\n<Roselitte>"...Even though you fell into the river on your own."

\n<Lyric>"What's with that? I saved you, so a little gratitude
wouldn't hurt, right?"

\n<Roselitte>"I wonder... We were the ones who saved you from drowning,
and we could have died in the process."

\n<Lyric>"Oh come on, everything turned out fine in the end. All's
well that ends well♪"
\n<Lyric>"--So, um... where did we leave off in our conversation?"

\n<Ameria>"The monsters attacked and then occupied the 'Fortress City
of Anatose'... that's where we were."

\n<Lyric>"...After you guys were captured, Deorc led the monsters to
attack Anatose to the east of the village."

\n<Lyric>"It happened in a flash. The monsters swarmed into the town
all at once, and the humans there couldn't put up much of a
fight and just ran away."

\n<Lyric>"Most of the humans who fled... um, what was that place
called again? The big town east of Anatose."

\n<Ameria>"...You mean 'Leve'? 'Central City Leve', it's the biggest
town in this region."

\n<Lyric>"Ah, that's it. It seems like most of the humans from
Anatose fled to Leve."

\n<Lyric>"And Deorc has stayed in Anatose, gathering a lot of
monsters. It looks like he's planning to attack somewhere
else when the time is right."

\n<Roselitte>"...The next target must be Leve to the east of Anatose. And
then further east, the 'Mainland of Valam'."

\n<Roselitte>"Has Deorc issued any statements... and do you know anything
about Prince Yuri's safety?"

\n<Roselitte>"Prince Yuri. He was taken away by Deorc during the incident
in the village."

\n<Lyric>"Taken away... Ah-, that handsome guy! I thought he was
quite a catch, so I remember him well. Heh, so that was the
crown prince, huh."

\n<Lyric>"But the crown prince is a very important person, right? Why
would he come to such a place?"

\n<Roselitte>"That was because of the imperial conference with Princess
Iris-- wait, were you there at that time?"

\n<Lyric>"Yeah, I was there.... Oh, and don't ask me to do something
unreasonable like saving you. With those monsters and
bandits around, there was no way to intervene."

\n<Lyric>"Besides, I was keeping an eye on Deorc's movements while
tracking your whereabouts. So I don't know the finer details
like any statements or what happened to the crown prince."

\n<Lyric>"But taking hostages like that means they probably won't
kill him for a while. But it doesn't change the fact that we
need to hurry."

\n<Lyric>"...Still, having the crown prince as a hostage is
troublesome. It's going to be difficult enough with Deorc
using monster taming magic."

\n<Ameria>"...I've heard of it. It's a real secret art that often
appears in myths and legends, right? But that means..."

\n<Lyric>"--Monster taming magic is a secret art that can only be
used by high-ranking monsters and a select few individuals.
So it's strange for Deorc, a human, to be able to use it...
is what you want to say, right?"

\n<Lyric>"In addition to that, there's another strange thing...
Knight. Since you've actually fought Deorc, you know this
'painfully' well, don't you?"

\n<Roselitte>"...He had abnormal strength unlike the first time we
fought. It was as if he wasn't even the same person."
\n<Lyric>"Right. And he said this: 'I have been chosen by God.'"

\n<Lyric>"If demons exist here, then gods must be somewhere too, even
though we haven't seen them."

\n<Lyric>"But even so, that's a ridiculous story. The monster taming
magic and that power must surely be the work of 'that'."
\n<Lyric>"Yes, 'that'... The one who gave Deorc his power is--"

\n<Roselitte>"He mentioned it in the cave as well. He said he was a
demon... It's hard to believe, but..."
\n<Lyric>"Ah... now that you mention it, I haven't said it yet."

\n<Lyric>"...I am an incubus. A succubus. The kind of monster you
despise."

\n<Ameria>"There's a reason why we live together at the church. It's
okay, so please put away your sword."
\n<Roselitte>"Living with a succubus...? Why on earth would you...?"

\n<Lyric>"Nfufu, something like this has happened before.... It's
fine. If you want to kill me, then go ahead."

\n<Lyric>"But wouldn't it be better to hear the story first?
Impatience is not a virtue, Knight-sama."
\n<Roselitte>"...If you do anything strange, I will cut you down."

\n<Lyric>"Yes, yes. I'll continue to behave myself just as I have
been."

\n<Lyric>"...Now, let's get back to the topic. The monster taming
magic and the immense power that Deorc acquired. Those were
given by 'that'."

\n<Lyric>"Do you remember? When the monster taming magic was used,
Deorc had a book in his hand, right?"

\n<Lyric>"The name of that book is... 'The Gluttonous Grimoire of
Begierde'."

\n<Lyric>"Both the secret art of controlling monsters and the power
to overwhelm you, Knight-sama, must surely have been granted
by that grimoire."

Roselitte and Ameria exchanged glances with puzzled
expressions.

\n<Roselitte>"The grimoire granted power...? Can such a thing really be
possible?"

\n<Roselitte>"Certainly, there are several grimoires known to contain
secret and forbidden arts... but from the way you speak..."

\n<Lyric>"Yes. Begierde is alive. It has a will and a purpose when it
grants power."

\n<Ameria>"...But even if that's true, why would Begierde grant power
to Deorc?"

\n<Lyric>"Who knows? That's what I'd like to find out too. But if
there's a connection..."
Lyric turned her gaze to Roselitte.

\n<Lyric>"It would be unnatural if there wasn't a connection. Did you
do something to incur Begierde's wrath?"

\n<Roselitte>"I don't know anything about that... I read books often, but
I've never done anything to harm them."
\n<Lyric>"--Haha! What's that? You say some funny things."
\n<Ameria>"...Okay, Professor Lyric. I have another question."

\n<Ameria>"'The Gluttonous Grimoire of Begierde.' What does
'gluttonous' mean in this context?"

\n<Lyric>"Good question. But don't think too hard about it. Just as
the name suggests, Begierde is a 'grimoire that devours
desires'."

\n<Lyric>"But it doesn't just devour desires. Begierde is a 'grimoire
that fulfills the owner's wishes by feeding on desires'."

\n<Ameria>"...Eh, sorry, I don't quite understand. Fulfilling wishes
means, that... eh? What does that mean...?"

\n<Lyric>"...Calm down a bit. You're sounding quite foolish right
now."

\n<Ameria>"But... that's impossible. Fulfilling wishes just can't
happen."

\n<Lyric>"'Begierde performs miracles by fulfilling wishes through
'chronicling memories.' It feeds on the writer's desires and
uses them as nourishment. However, 'the quality and quantity
of the desires fed to it determine the limits of the wishes
it can grant.'"

Roselitte and Ameria exchanged glances, both looking
incredulous.

\n<Roselitte>"Thieves attacked the village, Ameria was kidnapped, and
then Begierde appeared. Furthermore, you're living with
Ameria and you know so much about Begierde..."

\n<Roselitte>"...Ameria. Succubi are demons that incite and excite
humans, leading them to corruption. Many have been deceived
by their words and fallen."

\n<Roselitte>"I don't know why you're living with a succubus, but she is
an enemy to us humans."

\n<Lyric>"...I've made quite the lengthy preface. Now, let me get to
the main point."
Lyric took a deep breath before continuing her words.

\n<Lyric>"The Gluttonous Grimoire of Begierde. I was once the owner
of that book."

\n<Lyric>"...Before, 'a certain female knight' did something terrible
to me. Then Begierde appeared and said this to me."

\n<Lyric>"'If you feed me the knight's desires... her lust, I will
grant your wish.'"

\n<Lyric>"'By corrupting the knight with lust and feeding it to the
grimoire... seeking revenge. If I did that, it promised to
fulfill my request.'"

\n<Lyric>"I decided to rely on Begierde. But then... after a while, I
changed my mind. I didn't want to lay a hand on that knight
anymore."

\n<Lyric>"'If nourishment of desires is needed to fulfill a wish, it
doesn't have to be that knight who falls. That's what I
thought, so I targeted unrelated humans instead."
\n<Lyric>"I corrupted many humans and fed their lust to Begierde."

\n<Lyric>"...But it was no use. Begierde wanted that knight's lust.
Without corrupting her, it wouldn't grant my wish."

\n<Lyric>"So I went after the knight. I got close, used her, and
schemed to feed her lust to Begierde... but..."
\n<Lyric>"...In the end, I was killed by that knight."
\n<Roselitte>"...Killed by the knight? What do you mean by...?"

\n<Ameria>"Lyric was brought to the church as a corpse by 'Stella
Onee-san'... my older sister. She asked us to look after her
for a while."

\n<Ameria>"...And then after some time, she suddenly came back to
life. Really."

\n<Roselitte>"--That's absurd. The dead coming back to life, such a
thing..."
\n<Lyric>"It's impossible. But there is one who can do it."

\n<Lyric>"The Gluttonous Grimoire of Begierde, which feeds on desires
and uses them to grant wishes. I, its former owner, was
resurrected... and then Begierde appeared."
\n<Lyric>"Knight-sama. As you say, this is not a coincidence."

\n<Lyric>"...But truly, I don't understand anything. Why I was
resurrected, what Begierde is thinking, I don't know any of
it."
\n<Lyric>"That's why I want to ascertain its true intentions."

\n<Lyric>"...Knight-sama. If you are heading towards Deorc, you will
inevitably come into contact with Begierde. That's why I
want to accompany you on your journey."

\n<Lyric>"Of course, I won't ask for nothing in return. If I am to
accompany you, I promise to lend my strength. I will fully
cooperate in the rescue of the Crown Prince."
\n<Lyric>"I won't get in the way. May I come with you?"
\n<Roselitte>"No, I cannot trust you. I will head to Deorc alone."
\n<Lyric>"...Well, I expected you to say that."
\n<Ameria>"Alone... what about me? Let me come with you!"

\n<Roselitte>"You are to accompany me only until we reach a safe place.
That was the promise, wasn't it?"

\n<Ameria>"...But it's dangerous to go alone. Besides, Roselitte-san,
you're injured."

\n<Roselitte>"...Please don't trouble me. Given the situation, I'm only
accepting your help because I have to, but I cannot allow
you to be put in danger."

\n<Roselitte>"Well, I did say I would go alone, but if we reach a large
town, there should be some soldiers. I will join them and
devise a strategy before attacking Deorc."
\n<Roselitte>"Fighting is our job. You should just stay put."

\n<Roselitte>"And as for you, succubus. Regardless of the circumstances,
I cannot travel with a demon. By rights, I should be the one
to slay you."

\n<Roselitte>"However, you do owe me a favor, and you have provided
valuable information."

\n<Roselitte>"For Ameria's sake, I will pretend I did not hear of your
demonic nature. Be grateful. I will ensure you too are
escorted to a safe place."
\n<Roselitte>"...That is, if you do nothing from here on out."

\n<Lyric>"Ah, is that so. Thank you very much, Knight-sama. I won't
do anything—promise."

\n<Roselitte>"...And furthermore, if everything you've told us so far is
true, all the more reason I cannot allow you to accompany
us."

\n<Roselitte>"...A succubus's wish, huh? Even without asking, I can
imagine what that might entail."

\n<Roselitte>"Last time, it was unfortunate that your 'vile wish' was not
granted. How do you plan to use me and Ameria this time?"
\n<Ameria>"Lyric! Roselitte-san! Stop it, both of you!"

\n<Lyric>"...I no longer have any desire to feed Begierde with my
wishes or to have them granted."

\n<Lyric>"On the contrary, it's because of that thing that I was
killed. I hate Begierde so much that I'd burn it right now
if I could."

\n<Lyric>"So I'm not thinking of doing anything to you guys at all...
Remember who it is you owe your lives to."
\n<Roselitte>"Hmph. Is that all part of your calculation too?"

\n<Roselitte>"...I will take the two of you to a safe place. That is as
far as I will accompany you."

\n<Roselitte>"And succubus. Remember this. Do whatever you want on your
own accord. But if you become an obstacle to me or the
empire, I will show no mercy."

\n<Lyric>"Really, you're so hot-blooded and stubborn. And yet you're
in such a battered state."

\n<Lyric>"Are your injuries okay? I'm actually worried about you, you
know."
Lyric pointed at the wound on Roselitte's forehead.

\n<Lyric>"That looks worse than it appears, doesn't it? From what I
can see, it seems like your head has taken quite a beating."

\n<Lyric>"You'll never be able to fight properly again... Isn't that
right, Ameria?"

\n<Lyric>"And you're still recovering from illness, aren't you? With
your body in such a state, I wonder if you can really do
anything. You might just drop dead on the way, not to
mention facing Deoruk."

\n<Roselitte>"...I'll quickly whip this weakened body back into shape.
And it's not like I've become unable to fight. This much is
nothing to me--"

\n<Ameria>"If you keep pushing yourself like this, you'll die for
sure. It could be soon or later, but if you continue to
overdo it, it will definitely happen sooner rather than
later..."

\n<Lyric>"...You are strong. If you get your weakened body back in
shape and push yourself a bit, you might be able to defeat
Deoruk."

\n<Lyric>"But do we have the luxury of time to do that? If we dawdle,
things might become truly unmanageable, and who knows what
will happen to the crown prince."

\n<Lyric>"Deoruk has enslaved monsters and gained immense power. Even
if we fight as we are now, our chances of winning are slim.
You understand that better than anyone, don't you?"

\n<Roselitte>"...So what are you trying to say? Even if we cooperate with
you guys, the chances of winning are still low."
\n<Roselitte>"Even you, a succubus, struggle against mere thieves."

\n<Roselitte>"...I have always carved my path through any difficulty with
my own power. I have the knowledge, experience... and power
to do so."

\n<Roselitte>"I am one of the twelve knights of the Varum Empire's
Imperial Guard. Roselitte Schwarz."

\n<Roselitte>"...Succubus. If you truly wish to accompany me, then show
me the trust and value that befits it."

\n<Lyric>"...Hmph. As expected, or should I say typical? Even with
your body in such a state, your attitude remains grand."
\n<Lyric>"...But well, I don't dislike that about you."

\n<Lyric>"Fine. If you want to defeat Deoruk, I'll make sure you
win."
Lyric slowly spread his arms and said,

\n<Lyric>"Just entrust yourself to me. If you do that, I'll lend you
the power to make your wishes come true."
\n<Lyric>"I am the wonderful girl who grants wishes. Lyric♪"
